Date: 12/4/2001
Source: NZ Farmer
Author:
Vol / Page: 28
Edition:
Quote: Analysis showed that bareness [of a sheep's rear end] related to total average dag score. Only 3% of lambs with no dags at all got flystruck compared with 49% with a dag score of four and 82% with a dag score of five.
